			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Mr Lava Lava's Guide to pulling Quavonis Firetail in PoFire<a name="67545"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Oct 20 04 1:57 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I will probably find out that there are much simpler easier ways to do this, but here's one bards efforts.  Hope it helps someone on their first pull.
<br />

<br />
<u><b>Buff setup/songs</b></u>
<br />
<b>Buffs:</b>
<br />
FoE: mainly for lev component, one less thing to worry about
<br />
PoS: Want max FR
<br />
Mage DS: see above (ps with song and PoS I take 36 dmg from lava, with Mage DS + song + PoS I take 34... so dont sweat it)
<br />
<b>Songs:</b>
<br />
DA: Must have, will <b>not</b> make it without
<br />
Selos: See above
<br />
Psalm of Veeshan (PoV): Will take over 100 dmg from lava without this
<br />
<b>Equip:</b>
<br />
EB item is just nice to have, I sometimes dont bother (ok ok, i forget)
<br />

<br />
<u><b>The Lava</b></u>
<br />
<b>That burning sensation</b>: Without bard song the dmg is over 100.  I think its calculated per second, definitely faster than per tick
<br />
<b>I'm blind</b>:  Visibility is awful, like 10 feet.  This is the single hardest thing about this.  You wont find tunnel until you are right on top of it.
<br />

<br />
<u><b>Getting there</b></u>
<br />
I'm assuming that you are pulling to the two bird camp, and that raid is setup in NE corner which i think is standard practice. When you head away from camp the golem platform has 4 legs.  Follow the North wall by the lava on same side as raid until you are past the second leg by a few yards and head down.  The entrance to the tunnel is surrounded by rocks, these are what you usually see first.  You won't find it easily the first couple of times
<br />

<br />
The tunnel (otherwise known as the U-Bend of Fire... reminds me of a certain curry actually) goes down a bit then slowly angles up till you are going vertically up.  Its pretty long.   When you finally reach the surface don't move, take a look round and get your bearings.  See where the tunnel is with relation to the bird and the wall.
<br />

<br />
<u><b>Getting Away</b></u>
<br />
This is a right ba***rd.   Once you have aggro'd bird you have about 3-4 secs to find that tunnel.  If you don't DA will drop before you have got away and you are toast... literally.   On the upside you will lose ALL body hair, saving on the wax treatment.   The big problem is that the tunnel entrance is under the lava, so locating it in a hurry is a pita. 
<br />

<br />
EDIT:
<br />
I have found a way to locate the tunnel with reasonable consistency.  Setup on the wall directly opposite where the bird is facing.   If you look at the lava you will see a kind of V shape formed of darker red colours in the lava.  The bottom point of the V is pointing at you.   The exit is between the two points of the V.   Since finding this I have been 100% on pulls... Famous last words!
<br />

<br />
<u><b>Pulling the Bird</b></u>
<br />
The bird is on an island, the edge of this island will block spells (and thrown items I assume) so you have to float up high.   I face the bird directly above where i think the tunnel is and just walk backwards until i stop going up, then...:
<br />

<br />
1) Refresh Selos
<br />
2) Move toward bird a bit and turn round to face wall, I like to have my back to the bird so I dont waste time turning around.  Look at the lava and locate the V which will be pointing away from you. There is a small but finite chance that you will actually get it right.
<br />
3) Back up and aggro the bird.  I used to just HoS to pull bird, but now I use Bellow for the extra range.  There is also a nice trick that you can cast DA and bellow JUST before it lands.  But if you bugger it up you have to wait for DA to refresh.
<br />
4) DIVE DIVE DIVE!  HAWOOGA HAWOOGA! Find that tunnel.  This is harder than findin the 'tunnel of love' on your first ever... nm, lets not go into that.... nm, let me rephrase.... Anyway...  Dive exactly between the two points of the V mentioned above and you will be straight into the tunnel.  If you find the tunnel quickly you are golden, if not you are dead.  End of subject.  
<br />

<br />
If you are the hero you have found tunnel, just run for your life, you wont get out of pursuit range, just hightail it back to raid.  If you are the loser, mem DA asap and get back in zone quick as possible and just get a corpse summon, dont mess around waiting for someone to drag.  Just get summon done asap.
<br />

<br />
It is a bit scary when you get out of tunnel, &quot;am i actually going up?, where the fug am i, where the fug am i going?&quot; in addition the bird might shadowstep you with the result that you are utterly disorientated and you wont know where you are till you get out of the lava.  But this hasnt been real problem, if you are out of the tunnel you have succeeded. 
<br />

<br />
Thats it, i had about a 50% success rate at first, sux to be me! But trust me it will become easier.
<br />

<br />
<u><b>Notes for other classes</b></u>
<br />
On the subject of other classes doing this:
<br />
1) FD is irrelevant, fade has nothing to do with this pull.  I usually fade once I see a small green hobbit tank firing arrows, but thats just my pathetic selfish desire to stay alive thus depriving you of your fun.
<br />
2) Resists, without bard song you will be taking 100+ dmg from lava. While this isnt a huge problem you might have to regen up once in the bird cave. A monk could mend, a pally could self heal etc etc.
<br />
3) DA, this is a MUST have.  For monks, I don't know if you have a DA discipline that will save you from attacks from behind.  Pallies should be fine.
<br />
4) Run speed.  I wouldnt like say this is possible without Selo's, though I have had Selos drop on the way out.  Only one way to find out and I leave that honour to you.  Can you use horses underwater? Would it be practical given that you have to wait a sec for the horse to get up to speed, then you miss tunnel and have to search a bit?  I doubt it.
<br />

<br />
So basically while it's possible for another class to do this (Pally DA might be the best)  the bard has the complete package of DA/Speed/Resists.  Also bard DA has only 2.5 minute refresh so if you mess up there's not a long wait if you mess up.  And I often do.
<br />

<br />
Reasons i have fugged up:
<br />
Cant find that bloody tunnel x many
<br />
Buff slots were full so DA didnt land  <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-3.gif" border="0" alt="Scared" hspace="2" />ops: 
<br />

<br />
Melo</span></td>
