				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Mr Lava Lava's Guide to pulling Quavonis Firetail in PoFire<a name="67605"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Oct 20 04 3:03 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I've died twice pulling him but gotten him out both times. Yeah, he's a right bastard of a pull and you simply cannot overstate how frustrating the visibility problem is as well as the danger of not being able to find that tunnel entrance.
<br />

<br />
Personally, I to my timing a bit differently.  I tag him, dive for the lava and find the entrance, count to three after I start moving, and then hit DA.  The one time I used DA early, I died just as I emerged from the lave on the outside.  But I have never gotten out of that lava at over 30% health.
<br />

<br />
One of the cleanest pulls we did was a chain between me and a monk.  The monk got fire elemental illusion, I targeted Qavonis through him, monk did the pull, brought him into the tunnel and feigned and I tagged with bellow.  I couldn't see Qavonis at all, but I had him targeted and despite the crappy visibility, I had line of sight in game terms and that worked just dandy.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
